"Giddings L., Soto M.","Participation of Latin America and the caribbean in the global climatological records, GHCN [Participación de América Latina y del caribe en los registros globales climatológicos, GHCN]",2006,"Interciencia","31","9",,"632","637",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-33846811698&partnerID=40&md5=14be9f9102da330c7d35b9854e965652","Instituto de Ecología, AC, Xalapa, Mexico; Instituto de Ecología AC, Xalapa, Veracruz. 991070, Mexico","Giddings, L., Instituto de Ecología, AC, Xalapa, Mexico; Soto, M., Instituto de Ecología, AC, Xalapa, Mexico, Instituto de Ecología AC, Xalapa, Veracruz. 991070, Mexico","It is impossible to overestimate the importance of historical meteorological records for studies of global climate change. Many of these studies are based on data in GHCN, the Global Historical Climatology Network, a meteorological data compilation available over the Internet that is comprised of voluntary contributions from all over the world. Even though the participation of countries is worthy of note, it should also be recognized that their contributions vary in quality and quantity, and especially in being up to date. Data of many Latin American countries are incomplete and not up to date, which can cause errors in studies based on these data. Tables and figures show the participation of countries. In the name of researchers of climate change, the authors urge the authorities of all countries to change their policies so that their contributions to GHCN will be more complete and up to date.",,,,,,,,"Alexander, L.V., Zhang, X., Peterson, T.C., Caesar, J., Gleason, B., Klein Tank, A., Haylock, M., Vázquez-Aguirre, J.L., (2006) Global observed changes in daily climate extremes of temperature and precipitation. J. Geophys. Res, p. 111. , D05109, doi: 10.1029/2005JD006290; (2005) Global Historical Climatology Network, , www.ncdc.noaa.gov/oa/climate/research/ghcn/ghcn.html, GHCN; GHCN (2005b) Global Historical Climatology Network. www.ncdc.noaa.gov/cgi-bin/res40.pl?page=ghcn.html, después www.ncdc.noaa.gov/oa/pub/data/ghcn/v2/ghcnftp.html o www.ncdc.noaa.gov/oa/pub/ data/ghcn/v2/ghcnftp_zipd.html para acceso directo a los datos(2005) Index of Global Historical Climatology Network, , www.ncdc.noaa.gov/pub/data/ghcn/daily, GHCN; Gleason, B.E., Peterson, T.C., Groisman, P.Y., Vose, R.S., Ezell, D.S., A new global daily temperature and precipitation dataset (2002) 13th Symp. on Global Change Studies, , Orlando, FL, EEUU; Green, P.M., Legler, D.M., Miranda-V, C.J., O'Brien, J.J., The North American Climate Patterns Associated with the El Niño-Southern Oscillation (1997) Coaps Project Series, 97 -1. , www.coaps.fsu.edu/lib/booklet, Florida State University. Tallahassee, FL, EEUU; VASClimO, Variability Analysis of Surface Climate Observations (2005) Servicio Meteorológico Alemán y Johann Wolfgang Goethe-University, , www.dwd.de/en/FundE/Klima/KLIS/int/GPCC/ Projects/VASClimO/VASClimO.htm, Frankfurt, Alemania; (1990) World Weather Records, , www.wmo.ch/web/wcp/wcdmp/wwr/ html/introwwr.html, WWR","Giddings, L.; Instituto de Ecología, AC, Xalapa, Mexico",,,,,,,,03781844,,,,"Spanish","Interciencia",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-33846811698
